# NET-NEW under lead-q3r1 (→ shopsystem-templates; new capability → assign_scenarios).
# Product authority 2026-06-29: a doctor shell command that "validates credentials
# and connections." This is the agent-vault check of the rendered "bin/doctor": the
# broker is reachable AND its CA is trusted by the leaf. It is the diagnosis
# counterpart to the brokered-CA delivery behavior pinned by scenario 200
# (@scenario_hash:7ce09202755b0503) — when that transport degrades, the leaf's trust
# file is a path string instead of a certificate and brokered-MITM TLS fails subtly;
# doctor surfaces that as an explicit named fail rather than a silent failure.
#
# WORK-SPLITTING: ONE check-behavior scenario (agent-vault broker reachability + CA
# trust). Siblings: 215 (@scenario_hash:a6f8c0656a9e1cd9, messaging-DB) and 217
# (@scenario_hash:5cf88671d3fab25b, CLAUDE_OAUTH); aggregate pass/fail is 218
# (@scenario_hash:027a4d836bb1ae43).
#
# Pins what doctor ASSERTS (check name, pass/fail, remediation hint, and a
# distinction between the unreachable-broker and untrusted-CA causes), NOT the probe
# implementation.
#
# @bc: and the reproducing @scenario_hash on dispatch are the Architect's; the
# block-only @scenario_hash below is the PO's authoring hash.
@scenario_hash:f55aa51f4bd138b3
Scenario: the rendered "bin/doctor" credential check for agent-vault asserts the broker is reachable and its CA is trusted by the leaf, reporting a named pass/fail line with a remediation hint on failure
  Given a "lead" shop bootstrapped by "shop-templates" with the rendered ops command "bin/doctor"
  When the operator runs "bin/doctor" in a session whose agent-vault broker is reachable and whose broker CA is trusted by the leaf trust store
  Then "bin/doctor" emits a check line named for the agent-vault broker connection (a "agent-vault broker / CA trust" check) whose status is an explicit pass
  And the same check, run in a session where the broker is unreachable or the broker CA is not trusted by the leaf, emits that same named check line whose status is an explicit fail
  And the fail line distinguishes the unreachable-broker cause from the untrusted-CA cause and carries a remediation hint naming the corrective action rather than only reporting that the check failed
